 right to the smelly source of the problem: the sewers.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 1.925003692413333e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a big embarrassment\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2510}, {\"ngram\": \"the smelly source\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2568}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewers\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cleaning up the Seine is a bit of a misnomer.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2599, \"end\": 2604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2613}, {\"ngram\": \"a misnomer\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not an issue of industrial pollution, and it's not about trash,\\\" Pauline Lavaud, an adviser to the mayor, said on Sunday.\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999999982119334, \"rank\": 1.7880080593474384e-09, \"text\": \"Pauline\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an issue\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2647}, {\"ngram\": \"industrial pollution\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"about trash\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2697}, {\"ngram\": \"an adviser\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2726}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2739}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This question of 'Are we really going to be able to swim in the Seine?'\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2822, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"This question\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"is tied to the idea that there is everything and anything down there and we have to clean it out.\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2927, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But even if there are a fewV\\u00e9libdown there, that's not the issue.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fewV\\u00e9libdown\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2964}, {\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 2992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The issue is the bacteria.\\\"\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The issue\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3003}, {\"ngram\": \"the bacteria\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the bacteria come from toilets, which join showers, sinks, and rainfall in the sewers.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bacteria\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3039}, {\"ngram\": \"toilets\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"showers\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3077}, {\"ngram\": \"sinks\", \"from\": 3079, \"to\": 3084}, {\"ngram\": \"rainfall\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3098}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewers\", \"from\": 3102, \"to\": 3112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The toilets are reliable; the rainfall, increasingly, is not, and causes overflow into the river.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3211, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The toilets\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3125}, {\"ngram\": \"the rainfall\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"overflow\", \"from\": 3187, \"to\": 3195}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3210}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sewer engineer's riddle: What do you get when you mix a gallon of sewage with a gallon of rainfall?\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3315, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gallon\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3278}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3288}, {\"ngram\": \"a gallon\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3302}, {\"ngram\": \"rainfall\", \"from\": 3306, \"to\": 3314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two gallons of sewage.\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Two gallons\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3327}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3337}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the Parisian sewer system dates from the middle of the 19thcentury, when Napoleon III embarked on his urban renewal campaign.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3421, \"end\": 3429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1841909140721834e-65, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Parisian sewer system\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3373}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3395}, {\"ngram\": \"his urban renewal campaign\", \"from\": 3446, \"to\": 3472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most famous of those Paris projects were Haussmann's boulevards, but they came with an underground parallel: a system of sewers with blue-white-and-green signs to match the ones above, all tall enough for a man to stand in.\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3499, \"end\": 3504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3519, \"end\": 3528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8560648071230328e-55, \"text\": \"Haussmann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an underground parallel\", \"from\": 3562, \"to\": 3585}, {\"ngram\": \"a system\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3595}, {\"ngram\": \"sewers\", \"from\": 3599, \"to\": 3605}, {\"ngram\": \"blue-white-and-green signs\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3637}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3655}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, most men-it was a bit tight for Paris Deputy Mayor Antoine Guillou, the towering 35-year-old in charge of the city's sanitation system.\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3741, \"end\": 3746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3811}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's sanitation system\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday morning, he joined a group of reporters in the city's sewer museum with a difficult assignment: explaining how Paris had made the Seine clean enough to swim in.\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 4015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3966, \"end\": 3971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3985, \"end\": 3990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday morning\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 3862}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3881}, {\"ngram\": \"reporters\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3894}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's sewer museum\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3921}, {\"ngram\": \"a difficult assignment\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 3949}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though, at that moment, it was not yet clean enough to swim in.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that moment\", \"from\": 4032, \"to\": 4043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us digress briefly on the existence of a sewer museum, legacy of a rich Paris tradition of sewer tourism.\", \"from\": 4086, \"to\": 4195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4162, \"end\": 4167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4092}, {\"ngram\": \"the existence\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4125}, {\"ngram\": \"a sewer museum\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4143}, {\"ngram\": \"legacy\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4151}, {\"ngram\": \"sewer tourism\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eug\\u00e8ne Belgrand, the father of the system and author of a five-volume sewer text sprinkled with Latin quotations, boasted, \\\"No foreign sovereign, no important personage, left Paris without having visited the collectors.\\\"\", \"from\": 4196, \"to\": 4416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4203, \"end\": 4211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e8ne_Belgrand\", \"score\": 0.9529505816115332, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Belgrand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e8ne_Belgrand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e8ne_Belgrand\"}, {\"begin\": 4292, \"end\": 4297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4206033263161243e-15, \"text\": \"Latin\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\"}, {\"begin\": 4371, \"end\": 4376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the father\", \"from\": 4213, \"to\": 4223}, {\"ngram\": \"the system\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4237}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 4242, \"to\": 4248}, {\"ngram\": \"a five-volume sewer text\", \"from\": 4252, \"to\": 4276}, {\"ngram\": \"No foreign sovereign\", \"from\": 4320, \"to\": 4340}, {\"ngram\": \"no important personage\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4364}, {\"ngram\": \"the collectors\", \"from\": 4400, \"to\": 4414}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Czar Alexander II and King Wilhelm I were among the visitors; there were sewer trains for visitors and boats with cushioned seats.\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the visitors\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4477}, {\"ngram\": \"sewer trains\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4502}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4515}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4525}, {\"ngram\": \"cushioned seats\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the musty barnyard smell of the brown rivers-rivulets, creeks, the roaring flow of the main Left Bank channel-seemed less unusual in that stinking 19th-century world.\", \"from\": 4548, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4648, \"end\": 4657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rive_Gauche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.311415502711904e-20, \"text\": \"Left Bank\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rive_Gauche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rive_Gauche\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the musty barnyard smell\", \"from\": 4556, \"to\": 4580}, {\"ngram\": \"the brown rivers-rivulets\", \"from\": 4584, \"to\": 4609}, {\"ngram\": \"creeks\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4617}, {\"ngram\": \"the roaring flow\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4635}, {\"ngram\": \"that stinking 19th-century world\", \"from\": 4689, \"to\": 4721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris was also proud of its sewers, which had drained the muddy, fetid mess of the Second Empire's streets.\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4728, \"end\": 4733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its sewers\", \"from\": 4752, \"to\": 4762}, {\"ngram\": \"the muddy, fetid mess\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4803}, {\"ngram\": \"the Second Empire's streets\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first sewers were built just for rainwater.\", \"from\": 4836, \"to\": 4883, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first sewers\", \"from\": 4836, \"to\": 4852}, {\"ngram\": \"rainwater\", \"from\": 4873, \"to\": 4882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, after much debate, it was decided that they should also be connected to household waste.\", \"from\": 4884, \"to\": 4979, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"much debate\", \"from\": 4897, \"to\": 4908}, {\"ngram\": \"household waste\", \"from\": 4963, \"to\": 4978}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Haussmann did not want disgusting fecal matter in the underground galleries; the night-soil industry wanted its fertilizer profits.\", \"from\": 4980, \"to\": 5111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4980, \"end\": 4989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8560648071230328e-55, \"text\": \"Haussmann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"disgusting fecal matter\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5026}, {\"ngram\": \"the underground galleries\", \"from\": 5030, \"to\": 5055}, {\"ngram\": \"the night-soil industry\", \"from\": 5057, \"to\": 5080}, {\"ngram\": \"its fertilizer profits\", \"from\": 5088, \"to\": 5110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Landlords did not want to pay for the connections to replace their cesspools, stinking pits that in addition to their evident health risks led most building owners to discourage fresh-water use inside buildings, lest the cesspool fill too quickly.\", \"from\": 5112, \"to\": 5359, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Landlords\", \"from\": 5112, \"to\": 5121}, {\"ngram\": \"the connections\", \"from\": 5146, \"to\": 5161}, {\"ngram\": \"their cesspools\", \"from\": 5173, \"to\": 5188}, {\"ngram\": \"pits\", \"from\": 5199, \"to\": 5203}, {\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 5212, \"to\": 5220}, {\"ngram\": \"their evident health risks\", \"from\": 5224, \"to\": 5250}, {\"ngram\": \"most building owners\", \"from\": 5255, \"to\": 5275}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh-water use inside buildings\", \"from\": 5290, \"to\": 5322}, {\"ngram\": \"the cesspool\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Public health prevailed, but with a major consequence: Like most older cities, Paris wound up with a \\\"combined sewer system\\\" of rainwater and sewage.\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5440, \"end\": 5445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Public health\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5374}, {\"ngram\": \"a major consequence\", \"from\": 5395, \"to\": 5414}, {\"ngram\": \"most older cities\", \"from\": 5421, \"to\": 5438}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"combined sewer system\", \"from\": 5460, \"to\": 5484}, {\"ngram\": \"rainwater\", \"from\": 5489, \"to\": 5498}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 5503, \"to\": 5509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When there is too much rainwater for the system, the emergency valves tip it all into the Seine, a safety net for the city.\", \"from\": 5511, \"to\": 5634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5601, \"end\": 5606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"too much rainwater\", \"from\": 5525, \"to\": 5543}, {\"ngram\": \"the system\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5558}, {\"ngram\": \"the emergency valves\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5580}, {\"ngram\": \"a safety net\", \"from\": 5608, \"to\": 5620}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5625, \"to\": 5633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Also, the sewer museum closes for high water about four days a year.)\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(Also, the sewer museum closes\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5665}, {\"ngram\": \"high water\", \"from\": 5670, \"to\": 5680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The billion-dollar cleanup, Guillou said, has come in three parts.\", \"from\": 5707, \"to\": 5773, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The billion-dollar cleanup\", \"from\": 5707, \"to\": 5733}, {\"ngram\": \"Guillou\", \"from\": 5735, \"to\": 5742}, {\"ngram\": \"three parts\", \"from\": 5761, \"to\": 5772}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First, the city made sure that all the region's informal housing-and especially the Bateaux Mouches and other riverboats-was connected to the sewer system.\", \"from\": 5775, \"to\": 5930, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5790}, {\"ngram\": \"all the region's informal housing\", \"from\": 5806, \"to\": 5839}, {\"ngram\": \"especially the Bateaux Mouches\", \"from\": 5844, \"to\": 5874}, {\"ngram\": \"other riverboats\", \"from\": 5879, \"to\": 5895}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewer system\", \"from\": 5913, \"to\": 5929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, water treatment plants were improved to filter and clean wastewater before feeding it back into the river.\", \"from\": 5932, \"to\": 6046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"water treatment plants\", \"from\": 5940, \"to\": 5962}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 6036, \"to\": 6045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Third, the city built what Guillou calls \\\"the underground cathedral of Paris,\\\" a storage tank at Austerlitz, on the city's east side, capable of holding 55,000 cubic meters of wastewater during storms like the one on Friday.\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6119, \"end\": 6124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6145, \"end\": 6155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.9998502402851402, \"rank\": 0.00014978214640433128, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 6055, \"to\": 6063}, {\"ngram\": \"Guillou\", \"from\": 6075, \"to\": 6082}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the underground cathedral\", \"from\": 6089, \"to\": 6115}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" a storage tank\", \"from\": 6125, \"to\": 6141}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's east side\", \"from\": 6160, \"to\": 6180}, {\"ngram\": \"55,000 cubic meters\", \"from\": 6201, \"to\": 6220}, {\"ngram\": \"wastewater\", \"from\": 6224, \"to\": 6234}, {\"ngram\": \"storms\", \"from\": 6242, \"to\": 6248}, {\"ngram\": \"the one\", \"from\": 6254, \"to\": 6261}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 6265, \"to\": 6271}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a Parisian version of a \\\"deep tunnel,\\\" the kind of massive underground wastewater storage containers that have been constructed in Chicago, Washington, and other U.S. cities to comply with the Clean Water Act.\", \"from\": 6273, \"to\": 6487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6409, \"end\": 6416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9509968333056706e-21, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}, {\"begin\": 6418, \"end\": 6428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.5770154839214487e-11, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Parisian version\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6296}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"deep tunnel\", \"from\": 6300, \"to\": 6314}, {\"ngram\": \"massive underground wastewater storage containers\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6378}, {\"ngram\": \"other U.S. cities\", \"from\": 6434, \"to\": 6451}, {\"ngram\": \"the Clean Water Act\", \"from\": 6467, \"to\": 6486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the basin came online in May, Paris has not dumped any wastewater into the Seine.\", \"from\": 6488, \"to\": 6575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6524, \"end\": 6529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6569, \"end\": 6574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the basin\", \"from\": 6494, \"to\": 6503}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 6519, \"to\": 6522}, {\"ngram\": \"any wastewater\", \"from\": 6545, \"to\": 6559}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately for the triathletes, the Seine does not begin in Paris.\", \"from\": 6577, \"to\": 6646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6616, \"end\": 6621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 6640, \"end\": 6645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the triathletes\", \"from\": 6595, \"to\": 6610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The current water-quality problems are the fault of communities upstream, officials say, exacerbated by the fact the river is currently flowing at four times its normal summer speed after a record-breaking rainy spring.\", \"from\": 6647, \"to\": 6866, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The current water-quality problems\", \"from\": 6647, \"to\": 6681}, {\"ngram\": \"the fault\", \"from\": 6686, \"to\": 6695}, {\"ngram\": \"communities\", \"from\": 6699, \"to\": 6710}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 6721, \"to\": 6730}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 6751, \"to\": 6759}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 6760, \"to\": 6769}, {\"ngram\": \"four times its normal summer speed\", \"from\": 6794, \"to\": 6828}, {\"ngram\": \"a record-breaking rainy spring\", \"from\": 6835, \"to\": 6865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The watershed that contributes to Parisian water quality has effectively grown.\", \"from\": 6867, \"to\": 6946, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The watershed\", \"from\": 6867, \"to\": 6880}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisian water quality\", \"from\": 6901, \"to\": 6923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Olympics organizers, athletes, international media, and the city of Paris, the occurrence of Wednesday's triathlons seemed to be a judgment on the success or failure of cleaning the Seine.\", \"from\": 6948, \"to\": 7140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7020, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7134, \"end\": 7139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics organizers\", \"from\": 6952, \"to\": 6971}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6973, \"to\": 6981}, {\"ngram\": \"international media\", \"from\": 6983, \"to\": 7002}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 7008, \"to\": 7016}, {\"ngram\": \"the occurrence\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7041}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday's triathlons\", \"from\": 7045, \"to\": 7067}, {\"ngram\": \"a judgment\", \"from\": 7081, \"to\": 7091}, {\"ngram\": \"the success\", \"from\": 7095, \"to\": 7106}, {\"ngram\": \"failure\", \"from\": 7110, \"to\": 7117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that gets it backward.\", \"from\": 7141, \"to\": 7167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics may have motivated the region to get its act together, but the real achievement is restoring the river-not for a specific day but in general.\", \"from\": 7168, \"to\": 7322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 7168, \"to\": 7180}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 7200, \"to\": 7210}, {\"ngram\": \"its act\", \"from\": 7218, \"to\": 7225}, {\"ngram\": \"the real achievement\", \"from\": 7240, \"to\": 7260}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 7274, \"to\": 7283}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific day\", \"from\": 7292, \"to\": 7306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were just three species of fish in the Seine when Mayor Jacques Chirac promised that it would one day be swimmable; now there are 36.\", \"from\": 7323, \"to\": 7462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7368, \"end\": 7373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 7385, \"end\": 7399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Ch